Fischer Random (or Chess960) is one of the most popular chess variants in the 
world. The rules are all the same, except for the starting position of the 
pieces, which can be in one of 960 semi-random setups. Watch the best players 
in the world throw all of their opening preparation away and play purely on 
skill, speed, and intuition. 

